JOHANNESBURG - The Democratic Alliance is calling for a full-scale Parliamentary inquiry into power utility, Eskom.It's highlighted the reappointment of Brian Molefe as CEO and other governance failures.Parliament s Portfolio Committee on Public Enterprises is requesting all documents pertaining to the board's decision to reinstate Molefe.READ: Eskom board faces Parliamentary probeThe committee says an inquiry will determine if the board is acting in good faith.The DA also wants Public Enterprises Minister Lynne Brown to make submissions for the inquiry.The ANC says it too wants Parliamentary action taken against Eskom. Brown and the Eskom board appeared before Parliament on Tuesday to discuss Molefe s controversial return.eNCA